<TITLE> Hit by bus, indigenous man dies in Shahbagh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 16 (bdnews24.com) An indigenous youth was killed on Thursday when a bus hit him in Shahbagh crossing in the capital, police said. Dipan Chakma, 25, a pathology department student of Comilla CCN Medical Polytechnic Institute, had been doing internship at the Dhaka Medical college Hospital since June. The body was sent to the hospital for autopsy. Sub-inspector Mohammad Shafique of Shahbagh Police Station said that Dipan was crossing the road when the Rangdhonu Paribahan bus hit him at around 10:30am. People detained the bus and its driver Shamim and handed him to police. Some indigenous people smashed two buses and pelted some vehicles with stones at the scene of the accident at around 12:45 pm. Police chased and dispersed the demonstrators at around 1pm. bdnew
